<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 17 at 1:02PM CDT  by NWS Mobile</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southwestern Butler
and central Conecuh Counties through 145 PM CDT...
At 102 PM CDT, National Weather Service doppler radar indicated a
strong thunderstorm 9 miles east of Peterman, or 11 miles northwest
of Evergreen, moving east at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
McKenzie.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
